        "details": {
            "description": "<p>A roiling sphere of chromatic energy floats above a pedestal marked with arcane symbols.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[nature|dc:42] (legendary) or @Check[crafting|dc:45] (master) to remove an immunity the prison currently has to one of the following damage types: acid, cold, electricity, or fire (this effect lasts until the prison uses its Energy Immunity reaction to regain that immunity); @Check[arcana|dc:42] (master) to fortify the pedestal's containment runes, preventing the prison from using its Chromatic Eruption action for 1 round and causing it to suffer feedback that inflicts @Damage[20[untyped]] damage (this damage bypasses the prison's hardness and immunities); @Check[thievery|dc:42] (master) or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Dispel Magic] (8th rank; counteract DC 34) to suppress the pedestal's containment runes for 1 round, preventing the prison from using its Self-Repair action and causing it to suffer feedback that inflicts @Damage[20[untyped]] damage (this damage bypasses the prison's hardness and immunities). Unlike most hazards, Aethusa's prison can't be disabled, but it can be destroyed by reducing it to 0 Hit Points.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 16
            },
            "publication": {
                "license": "ORC",
                "remaster": true,
                "title": "Pathfinder #220: Crypt of Runes"
            },
            "reset": "<p>The trap deactivates and then resets automatically when it repairs to its maximum Hit Points.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(2 actions) The prison uses its first action to Self-Repair. If the hazard has less than its maximum Hit Points, it then uses its Chromatic Eruption action.</p>"
        },
